omar integrals. Besides, we show the validity\nof the Gauss phenomenon by explicitly relating near horizon charges with fluxes\nand charges computed by other techniques. All this provides a method to derive\nthe thermodynamics of magnetized horizons in a quite succinct way, including\nthe case of horizons exhibiting the Meissner effect.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2023 20:56:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 29 Apr 2023 15:56:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-02"}
